<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="178" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[140,1108,237,474]" box="[140,259,237,263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,259,237,263]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="178" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[140,1108,237,474]" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">
Tarsal formula 4-4-5 (most North American species) or 4-4-4 (European, African and Brazilian species) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lohse GA" box="[342,477,307,333]" pageId="3" pageNumber="178" refId="ref4671" refString="Lohse GA (1974) Staphylinidae II (Hypocyphtinae und Aleocharinae) Pselaphidae. In: Freude, Harde, Lohse (Eds). Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. 5. Goecke &amp; Evers Verlag, Krefeld, 381 pp." type="book" year="1974">Lohse 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Haghebaert G" box="[487,685,307,333]" pageId="3" pageNumber="178" pagination="223 - 234" refId="ref4436" refString="Haghebaert G (1991) A review of the Diglotta of the world (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). Bulletin et Annales de la Societe Royale Belge d'Entomologie 127: 223 - 234." type="journal article" year="1991">Haghebaert 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe JS" box="[695,816,307,333]" pageId="3" pageNumber="178" pagination="271 - 418" refId="ref4043" refString="Ashe JS (2001) Keys to the tribes and genera of Nearctic Aleocharinae. In: Arnett RH, Thomas MC (Eds) American Beetles, 1. Archostemata, Myxophaga, Adepahaga, Polyphaga: Staphyliniformia. CRC Press, Boca Raton, Florida, 271 - 418 pp." type="book chapter" year="2001">Ashe 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Caron E &amp; Ribeiro-Costa CS" pageId="3" pageNumber="178" pagination="52 - 58" refId="ref4210" refString="Caron E, Ribeiro-Costa CS (2008) First record of the tribe Diglottini from South America with description of Diglotta brasiliensis n. sp. (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). Zootaxa 1776: 52 - 58." type="journal article" year="2008">Caron and Ribeiro-Costa 2008</bibRefCitation>
); claws strong, scythe-like; glossae thin and extremely elongate, protruding beyond labrum (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" box="[305,405,378,404]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Myllaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[305,405,378,404]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Myllaena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like); labial palpi thin, strongly elongate, and stylate (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1089,378,404]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1643,1665]" captionTargetBox="[214,1032,185,1611]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1046,165,1624]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Diglotta mersa (Haliday) in dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); maxillae elongate, maxillary lobes long, with scattered teeth on lacinia (
<figureCitation box="[967,1034,413,439]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1643,1665]" captionTargetBox="[214,1032,185,1611]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1046,165,1624]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Diglotta mersa (Haliday) in dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); eyes small (
<figureCitation box="[213,277,448,474]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1643,1665]" captionTargetBox="[214,1032,185,1611]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1046,165,1624]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Diglotta mersa (Haliday) in dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); body form distinct (
<figureCitation box="[526,590,448,474]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1643,1665]" captionTargetBox="[214,1032,185,1611]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[202,1046,165,1624]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Diglotta mersa (Haliday) in dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="178">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
